narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class is very interesting and the grading is fair, but there are a lot of readings assigned. They take a lot of time and don't always get discussed in class.
It is a lot of work but in the end it is worth it. You learn a lot about modern french culture and the challenges the country faces today. Your speaking skills sky rocket.
Brilliant class. But make sure your spoken French is good and comfortable *before* you take this class as otherwise there's much that'll go over your head.

FREN 160 is a great course for anyone looking to learn more about France and improve their writing and speaking! I took the course CREDIT/D/FAIL because I wanted to keep practicing my french. I wouldn't recommend doing so because you still have to do enough work that it makes sense to just take it for a grade! I chose Madame Bergougnou over Madame Pinzka because (our semester) the class size was smaller and I liked that Madame Bergougnou was from France. I preferred Madame Bergougnou - she was fantastic!

This is a great comprehensive course that will greatly help you improve your french comprehension! The material and in-class assignments are very interesting. This class requires time. Reading assignments are long.

I would recommend French 160 to any student hoping to improve his or her understanding of modern French culture, as well as writing and/or spoken skills. The class is an overview of French politics, education, familial structure, geography, international trade, and many other relevant topics.
